author: Inside Edition
description: Police body camera footage showed two sisters fresh off a Florida vacation getting arrested at the airport. A flight attendant told police the sisters pushed her down. The sisters were taken into custody and charged with battery and disorderly intoxication. In an Inside Edition exclusive, the sisters tell their side of the story. Inside Edition reached out to Frontier Airlines and were told, "No comment." The charges were dropped after the sisters completed a pretrial intervention program.
title: 'Sunburned Sisters' Speak Out After Airport Arrest

author: Inside Edition
description: It is a popular film, and now the movie "Wicked" is the inspiration for some great Halloween costumes this year. Three models show how you can dress up as Glinda, Elfaba, and the cowardly lion from the movie "Wicked." And, no couple has gotten more attention than Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce. Swift and Kelce are a great go-to couples costume for Halloween 2025. Labubus were the hottest accessory of the year. They are furry, elf-like creatures with toothy grins, another great costume idea.
title: Here Are Some Halloween Costume Ideas For 2025

author: Inside Edition
description: Footage shows a sheriff fatally shooting a judge inside his judicial chambers. Judge Kevin Mullins can be seen trying to reason with Kentucky sheriff Shawn Stines before he opened fire. Investigators say moments before the shooting, Stines used Mullins' phone to call his teenage daughter, whose number was apparently saved in the judge's phone. Rumors flew that the judge was in a relationship with the daughter. Stines' daughter, Lila Stines, addressed the rumors in a series of TikTok videos.
title: Daughter Of Kentucky Sheriff Who Fatally Shot Judge Addresses Rumors

author: Inside Edition
description: A teen was pulled over after cops say he was driving 106 miles an hour. Santiago Londono, 19, told the deputy that his mother was rushing him to take his younger brother home. Cops say the teen was driving across a bridge more than 60 miles over the speed limit with his kid brother in a passenger seat. The deputy was not buying his story that his mom was to blame. Londono was put in handcuffs and taken to jail.
title: Teen Blames Mom After Getting Pulled Over For Driving 106 MPH: Cops

author: Inside Edition
description: Two bandits dressed as construction workers broke into the home of a wealthy New York City jeweler and stole $3.2 million in jewelry and gold in their backpacks. People wearing neon vests with reflector bans and hard hats are a common sight, designed to make the wearer stand out, but some robbers are using them to blend in. Police fear that following the Louvre Museum robbery, copycat criminals will use the tactic more and more.
title: Bandits Dressed As Construction Workers Steal $3.2 Million in Jewelry

author: Inside Edition
description: Police bodycam footage from the day a teacher got shot by her first-grade student played in court Wednesday. Twenty-eight-year-old teacher Abby Zwerner is suing her school's former assistant principal, alleging that Ebony Parker failed to act after four people told her about concerns that the student had brought a gun to school. The boy's mother has spoken out saying he has a severe form of ADHD. Parker's attorneys say no one could have foreseen that a 6-year-old would bring a firearm to school.
title: Police Bodycam Plays In Court From Day 1st Grade Student Shot Teacher

author: Inside Edition
description: If your kids thought sitting in the car while it goes through the car wash was scary, this business just upped the game. From now until Halloween, an Anaheim, California, business is going by the Tunnel of Terror. Not only will the giant, moving machines be cleaning your car, staff is on hand to scare you and your passengers. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Car Wash Transforms Into 'Tunnel of Terror' For Halloween

author: Inside Edition
description: Nine-year-old #MelodeeBuzzard was last seen three weeks ago. Surveillance photos show her at a car rental business wearing a hooded sweatshirt and detectives say a very large dark wig, perhaps to disguise her appearance.
title: What Happened To 9-Year-Old Melodee Buzzard? #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: An incredibly powerful hurricane swept through Jamaica on Tuesday, leaving flooding and destruction in its wake. Hurricane Melissa was a Category 5 storm – and was reported to be the strongest storm ever to hit the island nation. Wind speeds were recorded at 185 miles per hour. Officials described the southwestern parish of St. Elizabeth as "underwater," leaving hundreds of thousands of people without power.
title: Powerful Hurricane Melissa Makes Landfall in Jamaica and Cuba

author: Inside Edition
description: Jody Plauché's father shot Jeff Doucet as police led the abuser through Baton Rouge's airport.
title: How Jody Plauché Survived Sexual Abuse, Kidnapping And More #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A speeding Porsche jumped a curb, slamming into a young man on a first date, then hitting a light pole. The driver, Kristina Chambers, claims her #highheels got stuck on the pedals, and that's why she could not control the car.
title: Driver Who Blamed High Heels For Fatal Crash Is Sentenced #shorts
